---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "About NomadBurn | Digital Nomad Runway Planning";
const description =
  "Learn what NomadBurn is, who it is for, and how the digital nomad burn rate calculator helps remote workers plan moves with clearer money assumptions.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/about/">
  <section class="content-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">About NomadBurn</p>
    <h1>A money reality check before the move.</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">
      NomadBurn helps remote workers, freelancers, and indie builders estimate how a city choice
      changes monthly burn, savings runway, and break-even income before booking flights or housing.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-grid">
    <article class="content-panel wide">
      <h2>Why this exists</h2>
      <p>
        A destination can look affordable until tax reserve, payment loss, fixed costs, coworking,
        insurance, and visa buffers are added. NomadBurn turns those hidden items into a simple
        planning model so you can compare scenarios with less wishful thinking, including newer
        Europe coverage for cities such as Tbilisi, Budapest, Prague, Warsaw, Belgrade, Sofia, and
        Bucharest.
      </p>
      <p>
        The goal is not to tell you where to live. The goal is to make the tradeoffs visible enough
        that you can ask better questions before making a personal, financial, or immigration
        decision.
      </p>
    </article>

    <aside class="content-panel">
      <h2>Best for</h2>
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>Remote workers comparing city costs.</li>
        <li>Freelancers with variable monthly income.</li>
        <li>Indie founders protecting runway.</li>
        <li>Nomads checking whether lifestyle creep is eating the savings advantage.</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="content-panel">
    <h2>How NomadBurn stays useful</h2>
    <ol class="number-list">
      <li>Keep the calculator fast, free, and usable without an account.</li>
      <li>Make cost assumptions visible instead of hiding them behind a black box.</li>
      <li>Label rough planning estimates clearly and link to the methodology.</li>
      <li>Use Search Console and user feedback to deepen pages that show real demand.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="content-panel faq">
    <h2>Important limitation</h2>
    <p>
      NomadBurn is educational planning software. It does not provide financial, tax, legal,
      investment, healthcare, or immigration advice. Use it as a starting point, then verify major
      decisions with qualified professionals and current local sources.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
